WEBVTT

00:00.533 --> 00:02.768
Dre:
<i>Dr. Martin luther king jr. --</i>

00:02.770 --> 00:04.670
<i>Visionary leader,</i>
<i>commanding orator,</i>

00:04.672 --> 00:06.105
<i>And disciple of nonviolence.</i>

00:06.107 --> 00:07.740
<i>No matter what</i>
<i>they threw at him,</i>

00:07.742 --> 00:10.776
<i>He always managed</i>
<i>to keep his temper in line</i>

00:10.778 --> 00:14.113
<i>And, arguably equally</i>
<i>important, his mustache.</i>

00:14.115 --> 00:17.049
<i>I mean,</i>
<i>this thing is always on point.</i>

00:17.051 --> 00:19.718
<i>So every year,</i>
<i>to properly celebrate</i>

00:19.720 --> 00:22.388
<i>Martin luther king day,</i>
<i>the johnsons partake</i>

00:22.390 --> 00:24.356
<i>In a longstanding tradition</i>

00:24.358 --> 00:29.094
<i>We in the community call</i>
<i>"black ski weekend."</i>

00:29.096 --> 00:30.729
All right,
johnson clan.

00:30.731 --> 00:32.231
Everybody fitting into
their ski gear from last year

00:32.233 --> 00:34.733
So we can tear it up
on Saturday?

00:34.735 --> 00:36.201
Yep.
Nope.

00:36.203 --> 00:37.603
What?!
I'm good.

00:37.605 --> 00:41.240
Oh, exactly.
I don't plan on skiing much.

00:41.242 --> 00:44.376
I plan on looking incredible
while I relax in the lodge.

00:44.378 --> 00:46.311
We are johnsons --
we ski!

00:46.313 --> 00:49.114
And ski and ski.

00:49.116 --> 00:50.149
And ski.

00:50.151 --> 00:53.152
Until all our tears
are frozen.

00:53.154 --> 00:57.122
Thanks again, mr. J,
for inviting me on your trip.
Mm-hmm.

00:57.124 --> 00:58.757
My family usually
teaches literacy

00:58.759 --> 01:00.826
At the local prison
for mlk day.

01:00.828 --> 01:02.361
How come we never
do anything like that

01:02.363 --> 01:03.796
For
martin luther king day?

01:03.798 --> 01:06.265
Uh, because we're black
all year long.

01:06.267 --> 01:08.100
They're white.
They have to do extra credit.

01:08.102 --> 01:10.335
Solid comeback. Yeah.
Thank you.

01:10.337 --> 01:13.639
Is about breaking down
the color barrier on the slopes.

01:13.641 --> 01:15.441
Zach:
Oh, interesting mlk fact --

01:15.443 --> 01:17.276
The sound system
for the March on washington

01:17.278 --> 01:19.678
Was sabotaged
moments before the event.

01:19.680 --> 01:22.781
Yeah, and robert kennedy
sent the army in to fix it.

01:22.783 --> 01:24.216
Come on. I can do this
in my sleep, rookie.

01:24.218 --> 01:26.385
So can my kids.
Hit him with it, zo-zo.

01:26.387 --> 01:28.353
Tell him about
the March on washington.

01:28.355 --> 01:30.856
Don't you mean the March on
washington for jobs and freedom

01:30.858 --> 01:32.224
Organized
by the big six?

01:32.226 --> 01:33.659
Boom!

01:33.661 --> 01:34.827
And, junior,
tell him what happened

01:34.829 --> 01:36.528
<i>At</i> the March on washington.

01:36.530 --> 01:39.698
Total game changer.

01:39.700 --> 01:41.233
People marched.

01:41.235 --> 01:43.168
Uh...

01:43.170 --> 01:44.536
On washington.
[ chuckles ]

01:44.538 --> 01:49.308
Where dr. King gave his
"I have a dream" speech, huh?

01:49.310 --> 01:51.210
Tell him about that,
son.

01:51.212 --> 01:55.214
I know the gist,
but I always kind of zone out

01:55.216 --> 01:57.483
When people start to tell me
about their dreams.

01:57.485 --> 01:59.485
A half a million people
traveled the country

01:59.487 --> 02:01.220
To hear that speech,

02:01.222 --> 02:03.489
And my son can't tell me
anything about it?

02:03.491 --> 02:05.791
Actually, mr. J,
I think the number was

02:05.793 --> 02:07.726
A little bit closer
to 250,000.

02:07.728 --> 02:09.228
Zach! Go home!

02:09.230 --> 02:12.898
Uh, you know what, zach?
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Come back.

02:12.900 --> 02:15.300
Give me my grape soda.
Now go home!

02:15.302 --> 02:17.736
Really?

02:24.444 --> 02:26.778
[ sighs ]

02:26.780 --> 02:30.449
Babe, I cannot sleep at a time
like this, all right?

02:30.451 --> 02:31.884
We raised
a bad black person.

02:31.886 --> 02:34.853
That white boy knowing
more about martin luther king

02:34.855 --> 02:36.355
Than junior
is an embarrassment.

02:36.357 --> 02:37.923
Look, there's certain
trailblazing cultural icons

02:37.925 --> 02:40.359
That every black person
should know.

02:40.361 --> 02:41.727
Agreed.

02:41.729 --> 02:42.761
Obama, tupac...
Uh-huh. Yep.

02:42.763 --> 02:44.463
...Dave chappelle.
Mm.

02:44.465 --> 02:48.233
Maybe even
above dave chappelle.

02:48.235 --> 02:50.836
To the martin luther king day
parade. Uh...

02:51.905 --> 02:52.905
Both: Nah.

02:52.907 --> 02:53.906
Nah, the food's not
that good.

02:53.908 --> 02:57.276
They never fully close
the street. You could get hit.

02:57.278 --> 02:58.777
Monday is<i> not</i> a great day
for a parade.

02:58.779 --> 03:01.213
Oh, my god!

03:01.215 --> 03:03.849
This is on us!
We're the bad black people!

03:03.851 --> 03:05.851
Mnh-mnh!
That's it. That's it.

03:05.853 --> 03:08.387
Time for a weekend-long
family refresher course

03:08.389 --> 03:09.788
On all things king.

03:09.790 --> 03:11.590
So...We're not
going skiing?

03:11.592 --> 03:13.625
We're gonna stay home
and relax?
What?

03:13.627 --> 03:15.260
Oh. Are we going to
the parade?

03:15.262 --> 03:16.762
Oh, god, no.

03:16.764 --> 03:18.931
So, we are gonna have a lot
to do on Monday,

03:18.933 --> 03:20.766
But I understand,
dre, charlie,

03:20.768 --> 03:22.768
That it's a holiday
for you two,

03:22.770 --> 03:23.936
So feel free
to take the day off.

03:23.938 --> 03:25.204
Enjoy that.

03:25.206 --> 03:26.205
Oh, I will.

03:26.207 --> 03:27.839
Hey, hey, hey.
Hold on, charlie.

03:27.841 --> 03:30.509
Uh, what do you mean
"feel free to take the day off"?

03:30.511 --> 03:33.845
Mlk is a national holiday,
not a black holiday.

03:33.847 --> 03:36.515
Obama's inauguration --
black holiday.

03:36.517 --> 03:40.552
O.J. Getting off --
black holiday.

03:40.554 --> 03:42.387
Roscoe's chicken and waffles
grand opening.

03:42.389 --> 03:43.922
Charlie,
please, don't help me.

03:43.924 --> 03:47.993
So, you mean to tell me
that one day a year...

03:47.995 --> 03:50.362
It's a white party
up in here?

03:50.364 --> 03:51.563
[ chuckles ]
well...

03:51.565 --> 03:53.999
[ spin doctors'
"two princes" playing ]

03:54.001 --> 03:55.867
♪ yeah ♪

03:55.869 --> 03:59.438
♪ one, two princes kneel
before you ♪

03:59.440 --> 04:00.839
♪ that's what I said, now ♪

04:00.841 --> 04:03.408
Stevens: Look, dre,
I hear you loud and clear,

04:03.410 --> 04:04.743
So we'll see you guys
on Monday.

04:04.745 --> 04:07.846
So now you trying to get me
to come in on king day?

04:07.848 --> 04:10.849
Man, you out your mind.
Charlie, let's roll.

04:10.851 --> 04:12.851
Trippin'.
Work on king day.
Yeah.

04:12.853 --> 04:14.419
We out.

04:14.421 --> 04:17.589
You almost had us working
on Monday.
Dre: Mm.

04:17.591 --> 04:18.890
That was too close.

04:18.892 --> 04:20.892
You know what's<i> too</i> close,
charlie?

04:20.894 --> 04:22.728
Our pee streams.

04:22.730 --> 04:23.795
Oh, that don't
bother me none.

04:23.797 --> 04:24.963
Uh, I see.
[ chuckles ]

04:24.965 --> 04:27.899
Oh, you know, just doing
a little martin luther skiing.

04:27.901 --> 04:29.534
[ chuckles ]
you see what I did right there?

04:29.536 --> 04:32.371
Uh, not really.
But it sounds fun.

04:32.373 --> 04:34.506
Me -- I'll be
at home alone.

04:34.508 --> 04:36.875
You know, eustace is gonna be
at his mom's house,

04:36.877 --> 04:38.877
And my selfish neighbor
finally put a passcode

04:38.879 --> 04:41.546
On the wi-fi,
so no internet.

04:41.548 --> 04:42.848
[ chuckles ]
mm.

04:42.850 --> 04:45.717
Guess I'll look through
these magazines I found.

04:45.719 --> 04:48.787
Got a<i> redbook</i>
with rachael ray on the cover.

04:48.789 --> 04:50.756
[ chuckles ]

04:50.758 --> 04:51.890
Yeah, but --
but skiing sounds nice.

04:51.892 --> 04:53.825
Mm. Yeah.
That's nice.
That's nice.

04:53.827 --> 04:56.295
I never seen snow.

04:56.297 --> 04:57.729
You've never seen snow?

04:57.731 --> 04:58.930
What is it like?

04:58.932 --> 05:00.966
Man, y-y-you want to come
with us, charlie?

05:00.968 --> 05:02.467
I'd love to.
Uh...

05:02.469 --> 05:03.869
Uh, wait a minute.

05:03.871 --> 05:06.004
The girl twin isn't coming,
is she?

05:06.006 --> 05:07.706
Uh...

05:07.708 --> 05:09.541
She's kind of weird.

05:09.543 --> 05:10.976
<i>She's</i> weird?

05:13.313 --> 05:15.781
All right!
Good news, guys --

05:15.783 --> 05:18.784
I've transformed our ride
into a multiplatform

05:18.786 --> 05:20.952
Audio-visual civil-rights
teaching machine.

05:20.954 --> 05:24.923
Who's ready to watch an uncut
version of "eyes on the prize"?

05:24.925 --> 05:26.925
Ohh.
[ sighs ] great.

05:26.927 --> 05:28.794
A 14-hour black-and-white
documentary

05:28.796 --> 05:31.830
Full of dog attacks,
assassinations, and hosings.

05:31.832 --> 05:34.533
Hey, I had to sit through
that justin bieber biopic.

05:34.535 --> 05:36.968
I'm allowed
to have interests.

05:36.970 --> 05:37.903
Rainbow:
It's okay, guys.

05:37.905 --> 05:42.808
Because some of us need some
downtime so we don't unravel.

05:42.810 --> 05:43.975
You know what I mean, dre?

05:43.977 --> 05:46.078
Tell me you understand
what I mean.

05:46.080 --> 05:47.679
Uh...
I need you to tell me

05:47.681 --> 05:49.981
Look in my eyes,
and tell me you understand.

05:49.983 --> 05:50.982
I-I understand.
Thank you.

05:50.984 --> 05:51.983
You're welcome.
Thank you.

05:51.985 --> 05:54.119
Oh.
I had to stop on the way.

05:54.121 --> 05:55.821
Slurpees and nachos
do not mix.

05:55.823 --> 05:56.855
Unh-unh.
[ chuckles ]

05:56.857 --> 05:59.691
You know what I'm talking about.
[ laughs ]
okay.

05:59.693 --> 06:00.859
What's up, junior?
How you doing?

06:00.861 --> 06:01.960
Zoey.
Hey.
Hey.

06:01.962 --> 06:03.662
Little white boy
I don't know.
Oh.

06:03.664 --> 06:04.863
Jack.

06:04.865 --> 06:06.898
[ sternly ] diane.

06:06.900 --> 06:08.800
[ sternly ] charles.

06:08.802 --> 06:10.836
Okay,
<i>that</i> is a cool car.

06:10.838 --> 06:12.504
Can we ride
with charlie?

06:12.506 --> 06:13.705
No, no. That does not sound
like a good idea.

06:13.707 --> 06:15.540
[ coughs ] mom.
What?

06:15.542 --> 06:16.908
Could I see you
for a moment?
Sure.

06:16.910 --> 06:18.777
If you get junior
in that car,

06:18.779 --> 06:21.913
You could probably get
reverend dr. Martin luther dad

06:21.915 --> 06:23.782
In the car with him.

06:23.784 --> 06:26.151
Ohh! Yes! Hey!

06:26.153 --> 06:27.719
Hmm?
Why don't the boys
go with you?

06:27.721 --> 06:29.020
[ gasps ] yeah!
Oh, no, no, not you.

06:29.022 --> 06:31.089
You're way too precious
to me.

06:31.091 --> 06:33.458
Good, because junior
is the bad black person

06:33.460 --> 06:35.093
Who needs educating.

06:35.095 --> 06:38.029
But after we get home, he'll be
a bona fide black panther.

06:38.031 --> 06:40.065
Actually, dr. King had problems
with the black panthers.

06:40.067 --> 06:42.768
Do you know who
the black panthers
had a problem with?

06:42.770 --> 06:44.770
Oh, d-- you know what?
That sounds great!

06:44.772 --> 06:48.140
You teach<i> your</i> car,
I'll teach<i> my</i> car.

06:48.142 --> 06:50.976
We'll see who's smarter
after we get up there.

06:50.978 --> 06:52.677
Okay. Well,
we know who's smarter...

06:52.679 --> 06:54.546
The car that doesn't have
the 14-hour documentary.
Mm-hmm.

06:54.548 --> 06:55.547
What?
Huh?

06:55.549 --> 06:57.582
Shotgun!
Seatbelts, please!

06:57.584 --> 06:59.050
All right,
so, once again,

06:59.052 --> 07:03.155
What was the outcome
of the montgomery bus boycott?

07:03.157 --> 07:05.524
Junior: Dad, what is this,
"black jeopardy"?

07:05.526 --> 07:07.692
I wish there<i> was</i>
a "black jeopardy."

07:07.694 --> 07:09.661
Come on right after
the "black wheel,"

07:09.663 --> 07:12.831
Then set me up for a night of
watching "the black blacklist,"

07:12.833 --> 07:14.966
Starring james spade.

07:14.968 --> 07:17.836
Then I'll watch the news.

07:17.838 --> 07:18.937
That's already black.

07:18.939 --> 07:21.106
Charlie, seriously...
Don't help me.

07:21.108 --> 07:24.643
Junior, montgomery bus
boycott -- what's your answer?

07:24.645 --> 07:27.112
We get to sit
where we want on the bus.
Mm.

07:27.114 --> 07:29.448
Dad, we're on vacation.

07:29.450 --> 07:31.450
This stuff happened,
like, forever ago.

07:31.452 --> 07:32.851
Enough with the trivia.

07:32.853 --> 07:36.521
Trivia? Is that what you think
this is, son? Trivia?

07:36.523 --> 07:38.857
<i>In that moment, it hit me --</i>

07:38.859 --> 07:42.461
<i>My son had no real</i>
<i>understanding of prejudice.</i>

07:42.463 --> 07:45.096
Junior, this isn't
just about history.

07:45.098 --> 07:47.799
Prejudice is alive
and well.

07:47.801 --> 07:48.967
That's the reality.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.869
[ siren chirps ]

07:50.871 --> 07:52.671
And boom.

07:52.673 --> 07:54.005
Ha ha!
Look at that right there.

07:54.007 --> 07:54.906
Right on time.

07:54.908 --> 07:57.242
Oh, god!
It's the cops!

07:57.244 --> 07:58.977
[ siren chirps ]
charlie, uh...

07:58.979 --> 08:00.111
I'm gonna hit
my nitrous.

08:00.113 --> 08:01.980
Hey, hey, charlie,
charlie, charlie!

08:01.982 --> 08:03.915
Relax, man.
Just pull over.

08:03.917 --> 08:05.784
[ siren wailing ]
all right.
[ breathes shakily ]

08:05.786 --> 08:06.818
That's one way
to play it.

08:06.820 --> 08:08.820
But we weren't
doing anything.

08:08.822 --> 08:10.155
Exactly, son.

08:10.157 --> 08:12.958
We're being pulled over
for dwb.

08:12.960 --> 08:13.959
Dwub?

08:13.961 --> 08:15.961
Driving while black,
idiot.

08:15.963 --> 08:16.962
All right, everybody.

08:16.964 --> 08:19.097
This is it.
Wallets in hands.

08:19.099 --> 08:20.932
No sudden moves.

08:20.934 --> 08:22.934
Zach, record this.

08:22.936 --> 08:25.604
If anything happens,
tell our story.

08:25.606 --> 08:27.005
On it.
[ beep ]

08:27.007 --> 08:28.773
[ knock on window ]

08:31.143 --> 08:33.044
License
and registration?

08:33.046 --> 08:35.013
Yeah, because
he doesn't think we have it.

08:35.015 --> 08:37.749
No, just
a routine question.

08:37.751 --> 08:39.918
Mm-hmm.
[ chuckles nervously ]
he's a diabetic.

08:39.920 --> 08:41.620
Uh, I'm gonna give him
some now & laters

08:41.622 --> 08:43.755
To get his sugar back.

08:43.757 --> 08:45.023
Sure,
like you ask everybody

08:45.025 --> 08:47.292
For their license
and registration.

08:47.294 --> 08:48.994
Stop playing, dre.

08:48.996 --> 08:51.696
Asking for license
and registration --

08:51.698 --> 08:52.998
We learn that
on day one.

08:53.000 --> 08:54.699
Oh, and what did you learn
on day two?

08:54.701 --> 08:57.168
How to pull over a car full
of law-abiding citizens?

08:57.170 --> 08:58.303
I'm not going back.

08:58.305 --> 09:00.906
I swear to god
I'm gonna hit my nitrous.

09:00.908 --> 09:03.775
We weren't swerving,
we weren't --

09:03.777 --> 09:05.944
Your tags are expired,
but I'm gonna let you guys go

09:05.946 --> 09:07.779
With a warning because
it's a "holiday weekend."

09:07.781 --> 09:09.648
Uh, you see that?

09:09.650 --> 09:10.882
[ breathing heavily ]
air quotes.

09:10.884 --> 09:14.052
It's a national holiday!

09:14.054 --> 09:15.921
Uh, so, mr. Johnson,

09:15.923 --> 09:17.889
Did you just want me
to e-mail you this footage?

09:17.891 --> 09:19.791
Shut up, zach,
and give me my phone.
Oh, okay.

09:19.793 --> 09:22.260
[ sighs ]
charlie, let's go.

09:22.262 --> 09:25.030
[ weakly ]
I'm gonna need a minute.

09:28.734 --> 09:31.703
<i>My effort to open junior's eyes</i>
<i>to the reality</i>

09:31.705 --> 09:34.706
<i>Of racial prejudice</i>
<i>was off to a slow start.</i>

09:34.708 --> 09:36.908
<i>Hopefully bow</i>
<i>was having better luck.</i>

