<i>Than a backwoods</i>
<i>convenience store</i>

10:59.026 --> 11:02.193
<i>Gratuitously named whitey's.</i>

11:02.195 --> 11:06.131
Hey, now watch him give us
the white-man once-over.

11:07.299 --> 11:09.701
Hey, welcome, sir!
How you doing?!

11:09.703 --> 11:13.038
Ah. Here we go
with this bull again.

11:13.040 --> 11:14.839
[ chuckling ]
what are you talking about?

11:14.841 --> 11:17.142
By his false friendliness,
all right?

11:17.144 --> 11:19.144
It's an old,
southern trick.

11:19.146 --> 11:20.879
All right? They call it
"the sweet tea."

11:20.881 --> 11:21.880
Oh, really?
Mm-hmm.

11:21.882 --> 11:23.214
All these things
have names?

11:23.216 --> 11:24.749
Yes, they do, son,
all of them --

11:24.751 --> 11:27.385
From the "alabama man slap"
to the "solange knowles."

11:27.387 --> 11:29.120
As we walk
through the store,

11:29.122 --> 11:31.189
Notice how he watches us
like a hawk.

11:31.191 --> 11:34.192
He's reading
a monster-truck magazine.

11:34.194 --> 11:35.960
Yeah, he's gonna hop up
any second, son.

11:35.962 --> 11:37.128
[ rattling ]

11:37.130 --> 11:38.863
[ coughs ]

11:38.865 --> 11:43.068
Damn it, jethro.
Time to take it up a notch.

11:45.038 --> 11:48.473
I...Am trying to make it look
like I'm stealing something.

11:48.475 --> 11:51.309
Shh! Shut up!
You don't know what's going on.

11:51.311 --> 11:52.410
[ coughs ]

11:52.412 --> 11:55.046
Ah! You found
the free candy.

11:55.048 --> 11:58.917
Take as much as you want, sir --
leftovers from Halloween.

11:58.919 --> 12:00.218
Damn it.

12:00.220 --> 12:03.054
Hey! What the hell
are you doing?

12:03.056 --> 12:05.490
Why, I must try it
before I buy it.

12:05.492 --> 12:07.859
Charlie!
All right, look --
I'm afraid

12:07.861 --> 12:09.394
I'm gonna have to ask
you all to leave now.

12:09.396 --> 12:10.462
Aha!

12:10.464 --> 12:13.865
What makes you assume
we're with him?

12:13.867 --> 12:15.166
Y'all got out
of the same car together.

12:15.168 --> 12:16.434
You walked in
at the same time.

12:16.436 --> 12:17.969
You just
said his name.

12:17.971 --> 12:19.304
See, son?

12:19.306 --> 12:20.972
I told you
we were being watched.

12:20.974 --> 12:22.140
Point proven.

12:22.142 --> 12:23.975
This is the world
in which we live.

12:23.977 --> 12:27.312
An awesome world where whitey
gives us free candy?

12:27.314 --> 12:28.480
[ sighs ]

12:28.482 --> 12:30.482
<i>Junior's extreme cluelessness</i>

12:30.484 --> 12:32.884
<i>Was making me frustrated --</i>
<i>and hungry.</i>

12:32.886 --> 12:35.887
Hey, you're making a --
really?

12:35.889 --> 12:37.388
I'll get it.

12:37.390 --> 12:39.124
Rainbow: Guys,
the car ride was really fun,

12:39.126 --> 12:41.459
But your father really
wants us to ski as a family,

12:41.461 --> 12:43.128
So we got to get back
on track.

12:43.130 --> 12:44.462
We got to wake up early
tomorrow morning.

12:44.464 --> 12:45.997
We got to buy
our lift tickets.

12:45.999 --> 12:47.966
We got to rent equipment.

12:47.968 --> 12:51.402
Ooh! Mom, check this out --
in-room spa service.

12:51.404 --> 12:53.004
Zoey.

12:53.006 --> 12:55.406
Three words --
"hot stone massage."

12:55.408 --> 12:57.909
Zoey, no.
We came here to ski.

12:57.911 --> 13:02.046
They wrap your feet
in greek yogurt.

13:02.048 --> 13:03.948
Book it.
I want a hot stone massage.

13:03.950 --> 13:05.884
I'm a bundle of knots.

13:05.886 --> 13:08.887
Me, too. This unit on fractions
has me stressed out.

13:08.889 --> 13:11.055
Book 'em. Oh, my god.
[ laughs ]
okay.

13:11.057 --> 13:13.391
You guys, is there actually
a chance that we might relax

13:13.393 --> 13:14.826
And have fun
on this vacation?

13:14.828 --> 13:16.828
I tried to show junior
some racism today,

13:16.830 --> 13:19.330
But it was thwarted
by the cops and whitey.

13:19.332 --> 13:21.065
Nope. No chance.

13:21.067 --> 13:23.535
Okay, so, dre,
I agree it's really important

13:23.537 --> 13:26.070
That junior understand

13:26.072 --> 13:28.940
That racism still exists
in the world,

13:28.942 --> 13:33.278
But we might not
run into that this weekend.

13:33.280 --> 13:36.981
<i>So I resigned myself to</i>
<i>a fun weekend without incident.</i>

13:36.983 --> 13:37.949
Thank you.
All right, thank you.

13:37.951 --> 13:42.554
Um, I was supposed to get,
uh,<i> adjoining</i> rooms.

13:42.556 --> 13:45.056
I'm sorry, sir.
That couple got the last ones.

13:47.059 --> 13:48.993
<i>And then there it was...</i>

13:48.995 --> 13:52.997
[<i> bell dinging</i> ]
<i>...My golden opportunity.</i>

13:52.999 --> 13:58.036
Oh. So, that couple got
the last adjoining rooms, hmm?

13:58.038 --> 13:59.337
Rainbow: Dre, dre.
What?

13:59.339 --> 14:00.905
Sweetie, it's okay.
Don't do this. It's okay.

14:00.907 --> 14:02.106
Bow, I'm not doing anything.
Okay.

14:02.108 --> 14:03.107
I'm being done to,
all right?
Mm-hmm.

14:03.109 --> 14:05.043
Junior. Junior.

14:05.045 --> 14:06.444
You see
what's going on here?

14:06.446 --> 14:09.247
I do. About to ruin my vacation
in three, two --

14:09.249 --> 14:11.249
Okay, listen,
ms. Lady, ma'am.
Here we go.

14:11.251 --> 14:13.918
You and I both know
that it's no coincidence

14:13.920 --> 14:16.421
That the only
black family here --

14:16.423 --> 14:20.058
Okay,<i> one</i> of
the only black families here

14:20.060 --> 14:22.360
Is being denied
fair treatment.

14:22.362 --> 14:26.130
I will not leave
until I get adjoining rooms.

14:26.132 --> 14:27.966
We just
don't have any left.

14:27.968 --> 14:31.069
Then make some, then!
This place is full of rooms!

14:31.071 --> 14:32.904
Knock down a wall
and adjoin a couple of them!

14:32.906 --> 14:35.573
That's our father.
Have you ever though about that?

14:35.575 --> 14:37.275
Our<i> father.</i>

14:37.277 --> 14:39.244
And he's not going
anywhere, either.

14:39.246 --> 14:41.613
Nope. He's one of
the "good ones."

14:41.615 --> 14:46.117
[ indistinct shouting ]
we'll wake up every morning, and
he'll still be there, trying.

14:46.119 --> 14:48.920
There --
there's nothing we can do.

14:48.922 --> 14:52.390
Oh,
nothing<i> you</i> can do.

14:52.392 --> 14:54.559
Well, there's something
<i>I</i> can do.

14:54.561 --> 14:56.227
Uh...

14:56.229 --> 14:57.495
I'm -- I'm so sorry.

14:57.497 --> 14:59.264
[ sighs, grunts ]

14:59.266 --> 15:00.331
Dre, what are you --

15:00.333 --> 15:01.966
What are you doing?

15:01.968 --> 15:03.601
I'm staging a sit-in.
What?

15:03.603 --> 15:06.371
Hey, son. Racism.
Take a stand.

15:06.373 --> 15:08.940
By sitting down
on a luggage cart?

15:08.942 --> 15:10.208
Adjoining!

15:10.210 --> 15:13.077
Oh, my god.
Adjoining!

15:13.079 --> 15:15.680
"ad-join" me, guys!
Come on!

15:15.682 --> 15:16.915
Sweetie, you made your point.
Let's get up. Okay?

15:16.917 --> 15:19.484
Oh, god!
Ohh!

15:19.486 --> 15:21.386
Did you
just "toddler" me?

15:21.388 --> 15:23.054
This is
a peaceful protest.

15:23.056 --> 15:25.123
I "gandhi'd" you.

15:25.125 --> 15:27.926
Gandhi inspired the world.
<i>You</i> are a giant baby man.

15:27.928 --> 15:29.360
Get up!
No!

15:29.362 --> 15:34.032
Get off the cart.
I shall<i> not</i> be moved.

15:34.034 --> 15:36.067
Wha...
Please, take him away.

15:36.069 --> 15:38.102
Don't bring him back.
Take him.
Junior, this is for you!

15:38.104 --> 15:39.470
I don't want this, dad!
King, I'm free!

15:39.472 --> 15:41.406
Just...Take him.

15:45.477 --> 15:47.145
<i>Finding myself unfairly</i>
<i>imprisoned like dr. King,</i>

15:47.147 --> 15:51.015
<i>I sat down to write my own</i>
<i>"letter from birmingham jail."</i>

15:51.017 --> 15:54.152
"freedom, like adjoining rooms,
is never given,

15:54.154 --> 15:59.991
But must be demanded
by the oppressed."

15:59.993 --> 16:01.626
Warm cookie?
No, thank you.

16:01.628 --> 16:03.461
Uh, excuse me.

16:03.463 --> 16:04.963
Are those
snickerdoodles?

16:04.965 --> 16:07.665
Yes.
Thank you.

16:10.102 --> 16:11.235
[ sighs ]

16:11.237 --> 16:13.104
Hey.

16:13.106 --> 16:15.406
I was beginning to think
I'd never see you again.

16:15.408 --> 16:17.308
I almost forgot
what your face looked like.

16:17.310 --> 16:20.144
It's been 12 minutes.
Look, you're free to go.

16:20.146 --> 16:22.013
And we were upgraded
to a suite.

16:22.015 --> 16:23.648
[ laughs ]
I'm a hero.

16:23.650 --> 16:26.451
Dre, I just found you
crying in ski jail.

16:26.453 --> 16:28.453
Okay, look -- I know

16:28.455 --> 16:30.121
I've been acting
a little crazy lately,

16:30.123 --> 16:31.723
But I'm worried
about junior.
Uh-huh.

16:31.725 --> 16:34.092
What?
We've sheltered him
so much.

16:34.094 --> 16:36.394
What is he gonna do
when something real happens?

16:36.396 --> 16:37.729
Sweetie,
I'm worried about that, too,

16:37.731 --> 16:39.697
But you're ruining
our vacation!

16:39.699 --> 16:41.699
[ sighs ]
martin luther king day
is supposed to be

16:41.701 --> 16:43.701
A celebration
of how far we've come.

16:43.703 --> 16:46.437
I mean, think about it --
when this resort was built,

16:46.439 --> 16:48.673
We would not have been
able to stay here.

16:48.675 --> 16:53.344
This resort
opened in 1988.

16:53.346 --> 16:55.513
Point is every time
I intubate a patient,

16:55.515 --> 16:57.281
I am reminded
of how far we've come

16:57.283 --> 17:01.119
Because of the accomplishments
of "dr. King."

17:01.121 --> 17:04.555
Did you just air quote
dr. King?

17:04.557 --> 17:09.127
No. I am a medical doctor
<i>because</i> of "dr." king.

17:09.129 --> 17:11.362
Are you hating
on dr. King?

17:11.364 --> 17:13.064
No, he is
a great man, dre.

17:13.066 --> 17:15.033
He has a nobel peace prize,
okay?
Mm-hmm.

17:15.035 --> 17:16.267
I do not have one.
Mnh-mnh.

17:16.269 --> 17:17.769
But if you were to have
a heart attack,

17:17.771 --> 17:20.638
He would give a great speech,
and I would keep you alive.

17:20.640 --> 17:22.640
I just don't understand
why we're called the same thing.

17:22.642 --> 17:23.775
It's just...

17:23.777 --> 17:25.276
Wow.
It's just...

17:25.278 --> 17:27.045
I really don't like
this side of you.

17:27.047 --> 17:28.079
What?
So I'm...

17:28.081 --> 17:30.048
[ tapping ]
...Tapping out.

17:30.050 --> 17:32.550
Well, go ahead and tap out,
but if you slip and fall,

17:32.552 --> 17:34.585
I'll just have to find you
a phd to help you.

17:34.587 --> 17:36.521
Oh.
You know, with a book.

17:37.523 --> 17:39.290
Charlie?

17:39.292 --> 17:40.491
We found him
by chair nine.

17:40.493 --> 17:42.160
He was holding two buttons
and a carrot.

17:42.162 --> 17:44.695
Snow ain't no joke.
Oh, my god.

17:44.697 --> 17:47.698
<i>The next morning,</i>
<i>I was ready to get my vacation</i>

17:47.700 --> 17:50.535
<i>Back on track</i>
<i>and do some skiing.</i>

17:50.537 --> 17:53.538
Charlie.
Are you wearing dress slacks?

17:53.540 --> 17:55.073
Don't worry about it!

17:55.075 --> 17:56.174
I'm gonna tuck 'em
into my socks.

17:56.176 --> 17:59.677
Oh, man.
I forgot socks.

17:59.679 --> 18:01.646
Sometimes when
I'm talking to the lord,

18:01.648 --> 18:04.849
Where's everybody else at?
[ chuckles ]

18:04.851 --> 18:06.684
You know, junior and zach
are on their way down now.

18:06.686 --> 18:08.820
Everybody else
must be on the slopes.

18:08.822 --> 18:10.822
Knowing them, they couldn't wait
to get out there.

18:10.824 --> 18:15.860
[ vibrating ]
oh, this...Feels...So...Good.

18:15.862 --> 18:18.729
Would you like plain
or vanilla greek yogurt

18:18.731 --> 18:20.298
On your feet, ma'am?

18:20.300 --> 18:21.732
Oh, one of each, please.
Mm-hmm.

18:21.734 --> 18:24.435
Left, plain, right, vanilla.
[ chuckles ]
mm-hmm.

18:24.437 --> 18:27.105
We'll find them
on the mountain.
Cool, cool.

18:27.107 --> 18:28.406
All right.
Oh, hey, junior,

18:28.408 --> 18:30.641
I want to apologize
for being an idiot last night.

18:30.643 --> 18:34.745
So I will not force my agenda
on you anymore.

18:34.747 --> 18:37.248
I'll believe it when I see it,
but cool.

18:37.250 --> 18:39.750
Yeah, all right.
Let's get on this bus.

18:39.752 --> 18:41.886
The racks are
for skiers only.

18:41.888 --> 18:43.888
Snowboarders and their boards
take the rear seats.

18:43.890 --> 18:45.623
But they're heavy.

18:45.625 --> 18:47.758
Wow, we don't get racks,

18:47.760 --> 18:49.794
And we have to sit
in the back of the bus?

18:49.796 --> 18:51.762
What are we,
second-class citizens?

18:51.764 --> 18:55.199
These nice resorts --
it's a skier's world.

18:55.201 --> 18:57.135
Ma'am, snowboarders sit
in the back.

18:57.137 --> 18:58.603
[ scoffs ]
can't you give me a break?

18:58.605 --> 19:00.805
The bus is half empty.
It's the rules.

19:00.807 --> 19:04.609
That's not cool.
She's old and tired.

19:04.611 --> 19:07.879
I'm only 40, and I slept
10 hours last night.

19:07.881 --> 19:09.881
Uh...

19:09.883 --> 19:11.315
This is crazy.

19:11.317 --> 19:14.452
Excuse me.
Can I say something?

19:14.454 --> 19:16.787
[<i> bell dings</i> ]
<i>and then it happened.</i>

19:16.789 --> 19:18.890
<i>When confronted</i>
<i>with actual injustice,</i>

19:18.892 --> 19:21.259
<i>Even if it was small-scale,</i>

19:21.261 --> 19:24.362
<i>In the spirit of dr. King,</i>
<i>junior knew how to step up.</i>

19:24.364 --> 19:26.831
I may be a newbie
to snowboarding,

19:26.833 --> 19:30.668
But the way you're treating her,
it's not right.

19:30.670 --> 19:35.173
There's no difference
between boarders and skiers.

19:35.175 --> 19:37.775
We're all just people
with wood strapped to our feet,

19:37.777 --> 19:39.777
Sliding down a mountain.

19:39.779 --> 19:42.713
I have a dream that one day

19:42.715 --> 19:45.883
We will not be judged
by the size of our board,

19:45.885 --> 19:48.519
But by what we do
in the pow-pow.

19:48.521 --> 19:50.521
Because the snow doesn't care
who we are.

19:50.523 --> 19:52.356
It does not.

19:52.358 --> 19:53.691
Snow plays for keeps.

19:53.693 --> 19:54.859
Uh...Okay.

19:54.861 --> 19:56.961
It just wants
to be thrashed.

19:56.963 --> 19:58.829
Free to thrash.

19:58.831 --> 20:00.498
Free to thrash!

20:00.500 --> 20:03.901
Thank god almighty,
we're free to thrash!

20:03.903 --> 20:05.269
[ laughs ]
[ applause ]

20:05.271 --> 20:06.938
Hey, that's my son,
everybody!

20:06.940 --> 20:09.941
My son --
a stand-up dude.

20:09.943 --> 20:12.777
Hey, that was
kind of impressive, son.

20:12.779 --> 20:14.779
I'm really proud
of you.

20:14.781 --> 20:17.782
It just didn't feel right
<i>not</i> to say something.

20:17.784 --> 20:19.617
I know that you think
I've had it so easy

20:19.619 --> 20:22.520
That I don't see what's up,
but I do.

20:22.522 --> 20:25.823
I'm a black kid in a world
where bad things happen to us.

20:25.825 --> 20:27.491
They can happen
to<i> anyone.</i>

20:27.493 --> 20:30.328
And that's why
I worry about you, son.

20:30.330 --> 20:31.729
And I worry
about you, too.

20:31.731 --> 20:33.564
But you've got to believe
that you've taught me enough

20:33.566 --> 20:36.534
To be careful,
but also brave.

20:36.536 --> 20:38.869
[ chuckles ]
you're right.

20:38.871 --> 20:42.540
It's really the same choice
frodo faced

20:42.542 --> 20:44.775
At the black gates
of mordor.

20:46.778 --> 20:48.779
All right,
back of the bus, nerd.

20:48.781 --> 20:50.314
[ both sigh ]

20:50.316 --> 20:53.651
Cannot have
a moment with you.

20:53.653 --> 20:54.785
I cannot.

20:57.523 --> 21:04.462
<i>A little bit of learning</i>
<i>and a lot of relaxing.</i>

21:04.464 --> 21:06.297
<i>In the end, it doesn't matter</i>

21:06.299 --> 21:08.299
<i>How you spend</i>
<i>dr. King's weekend,</i>

21:08.301 --> 21:09.934
<i>Just as long as you remember</i>

21:09.936 --> 21:13.537
<i>How he helped us all</i>
<i>make it to the mountaintop.</i>

21:13.539 --> 21:17.541
This is exactly what
I imagine heaven to be like.

21:18.677 --> 21:22.413
[ sighs ]
this is my hell.

21:22.415 --> 21:23.447
[ giggles ]
